---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Neutral Working" description="Luke Warrington. Product, QA, and delivery from Czechia.">

  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="container-narrow pt-16 pb-10">
    <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">About</h1>
  </section>

  <!-- Lead -->
  <section class="border-t border-border bg-surface">
    <div class="container-narrow py-10 space-y-5">
      <p class="text-base text-ink leading-relaxed">
        I'm Luke. I run Neutral Working from Czechia.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base text-ink leading-relaxed">
        I've worked in QA, development, and product for the last decade — currently agency-side,
        building features for iGaming brands, where the work ranges from leaderboard rollouts across
        six casinos to CRM platform migrations to "the launch is in two weeks and nothing works."
        Most fractional POs come from one of those three backgrounds. I come from all of them, which
        is why my engagements tend to leave behind systems rather than slide decks.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base text-ink leading-relaxed">
        I also build my own products under the Neutral Working brand. A football management roguelike
        (Kickoff Clash). A scouting platform for football clubs (Chief Scout). An e-commerce site
        (Crumble.cz). They're at different stages and they teach me different things — mostly that
        being on the receiving end of a vague brief is character-building.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base text-ink leading-relaxed">
        The brand is called Neutral Working because it's an anagram of my name, and because the work
        I do is mostly about removing drama from product delivery. Most teams don't need more
        excitement. They need fewer surprises.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How I work -->
  <section class="border-t border-border">
    <div class="container-narrow py-10">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-medium text-ink-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">How I work</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-4">
        <li class="text-base text-ink leading-relaxed">
          <span class="font-medium">Plain English over jargon.</span>{' '}
          If I can't explain a decision to a non-technical founder, the decision isn't ready.
        </li>
        <li class="text-base text-ink leading-relaxed">
          <span class="font-medium">Ship over strategise.</span>{' '}
          Strategy is the work you do to figure out what to ship. The point is still to ship.
        </li>
        <li class="text-base text-ink leading-relaxed">
          <span class="font-medium">Cut before adding.</span>{' '}
          Most products are 30% too big.
        </li>
        <li class="text-base text-ink leading-relaxed">
          <span class="font-medium">Systems over heroics.</span>{' '}
          If the work only happens because someone is grinding through it, the system is broken.
        </li>
        <li class="text-base text-ink leading-relaxed">
          <span class="font-medium">Honest scope.</span>{' '}
          I'll tell you what I think will and won't work before you've signed anything.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What I'm not -->
  <section class="border-t border-border bg-surface">
    <div class="container-narrow py-10">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-medium text-ink-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">What I'm not</h2>
      <p class="text-base text-ink leading-relaxed">
        I'm not a designer, although I work with good ones. I'm not a full-stack engineer, although
        I can read your codebase. I'm not a marketing consultant, although I'll tell you when your
        product positioning is hurting your delivery. I'm not a coach — I do the work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Where I work -->
  <section class="border-t border-border">
    <div class="container-narrow py-10">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-medium text-ink-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Where I work</h2>
      <p class="text-base text-ink leading-relaxed">
        Remote, primarily with teams in the UK, EU, and US East Coast time zones. I'm in Czechia
        (UTC+1/+2). I work in English and can run client-facing work in French if needed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="border-t border-border bg-surface">
    <div class="container-narrow py-16 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink mb-3">Ready to talk?</h2>
      <p class="text-base text-ink-muted mb-8 max-w-md mx-auto">
        30 minutes. No slides, no pitch. You describe what's going on, I tell you what I'd do about
        it. If we're a fit, we book the work.
      </p>
      <CTA label="Book a discovery call" href="/contact" />
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
